        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 4 at 6:54PM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 654 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms extending from 13 miles northwest of Clyde Park to 15
miles west of Livingston, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Livingston, Clyde Park and Wilsall.

These storms will impact travel on Interstate 90 from Bozeman Pass
to Livingston.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
